## 4. A project you've shipped recently

https://antigravity-clone-psi.vercel.app/

This is an interactive physics simulation inspired by Google’s Antigravity experiment. I built it using vanilla JavaScript and Matter.js, implementing realistic gravity, drag interactions, and dynamic rendering using the Canvas API. The project focuses on creating a playful and responsive user experience with features like gravity toggle, explosion, and drag-and-throw interactions. If I revisit it, I would improve performance for larger element counts and enhance mobile touch interactions.

## 5. Why you want to join Amber

Amber is solving a meaningful problem in student housing, making it easier for students to find and book accommodation globally. I’m particularly interested in how thoughtful design and frontend engineering can simplify such a complex decision-making process. The opportunity to work on a product that directly impacts student experiences and accessibility is compelling to me. I’m excited about contributing to a team that values clarity, usability, and building impactful products at scale.
